President Obama has nominated Allison Dale Burroughs and Amit Priyavadan Mehta to serve on the United States District Courts. Burroughs is a partner at Nutter McClennen & Fish, LLP and has experience representing individuals and corporations in criminal and civil proceedings before federal courts. She has previously served as an Assistant United States Attorney. Mehta is a partner at Zuckerman Spaeder LLP and represents clients in civil and criminal matters before state and federal courts. He has also worked as a staff attorney for the Public Defender Service for the District of Columbia. Both nominees have strong legal backgrounds and are expected to serve the American people with integrity and a commitment to justice.